The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for sarcasm detection, which falls under the scope of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of Context2Vec, a sentence completion library based on Bidirectional LSTM, suggests the use of deep learning techniques, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed approaches on different types of text data, which may fall under the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
